Well, 10m = 393.7 inches = 32 feet, 9.7 inches. For comparison, the Armstrong Whitworth Ensign (which had the same number of passenger seats as this ) was 34.8m in length, or 114 feet, 2 inches. If you prefer a jet, the Dassault Falcon 20 was a 40-passenger model, coming in at 17.15m (56 feet, 3 inches) with a wingspan of 16.30m (53 feet, 6 inches).

Of course it's bigger on the inside than on the outside anyway, so this really isn't germane.







